Abiodun Nejo, Ado Ekiti Stakeholders of the Peoples Democratic Party in Ekiti South Senatorial District, have resolved to compel Senator Biodun Olujimi, to contest the 2022 governorship primary of the party. The decision was taken after a meeting convened by a PDP leader, Chief Nelson Shaba, at Omuo Ekiti, in the Ekiti East Council area. This was contained in a resolution signed by representatives of the six local government areas which make up the senatorial district. A copy of the resolution was made available to journalists, in Ado Ekiti, on Sunday. The document read in part, stakeholders, “resolved to sink the differences among leaders and members to enhance a harmonious and peaceful implementation of the South Agenda. “The South Agenda Committee resolved to compel Senator Biodun Olujimi, to contest the 2022 PDP governorship primary, as a viable option of representation of the south senatorial district.” It was also resolved that local government representatives should revert to their respective local governments for further consultation and sensitization on the agenda while also agreeing to set up a sub-committee to reconcile aggrieved party members in the zone. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 